  "titleEn": "The Six Nouns - Case Endings",
  "description": "Learn how the six nouns change their endings based on grammatical case: nominative (و), accusative (ا), and genitive (ي).",
  "vocabulary": ["word-269", "word-270", "word-271", "word-272", "word-273", "word-274"],
  "grammarPoints": ["gp-051", "gp-052"],
  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Case Endings with و، ا، ي",
      "titleArabic": "إعراب الأسماء الستة بالحروف",
      "content": [
        "When the six nouns are in genitive construction (not with ي), they show case through letters instead of vowels.",
        "Nominative uses و (أَبُوكَ), accusative uses ا (أَبَاكَ), and genitive uses ي (أَبِيكَ)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Nominative (مرفوع): أَبُوكَ، أَخُوكَ (with و)",
        "Accusative (منصوب): أَبَاكَ، أَخَاكَ (with ا)",
        "Genitive (مجرور): أَبِيكَ، أَخِيكَ (with ي)",
        "These endings replace the standard damma, fatha, kasra"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ أَبُوكَ (مرفوع)", "english": "Your father came (nominative)" },
        { "arabic": "رَأَيْتُ أَبَاكَ (منصوب)", "english": "I saw your father (accusative)" },
        { "arabic": "سَلَّمْتُ عَلَى أَبِيكَ (مجرور)", "english": "I greeted your father (genitive)" },
        { "arabic": "إِنَّ أَخَاكَ مُجْتَهِدٌ", "english": "Indeed your brother is diligent" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Examples in Sentences",
      "titleArabic": "أمثلة في الجمل",
      "content": [
        "The case of the six nouns is determined by their grammatical function in the sentence.",
        "Subject = nominative (و), object = accusative (ا), after preposition = genitive (ي)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Subject (فاعل): أَبُوكَ كَرِيمٌ - Your father is generous",
        "Object (مفعول به): أَكْرَمْتُ أَبَاكَ - I honored your father",
        "After preposition: مَرَرْتُ بِأَبِيكَ - I passed by your father",
        "After إِنَّ: إِنَّ أَبَاكَ عَالِمٌ - Indeed your father is a scholar"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "أَخُوكَ فِي الْبَيْتِ", "english": "Your brother is in the house" },
        { "arabic": "زُرْتُ أَخَاكَ أَمْسِ", "english": "I visited your brother yesterday" },
        { "arabic": "تَكَلَّمْتُ مَعَ أَخِيكَ", "english": "I spoke with your brother" },
        { "arabic": "حَمُوهَا رَجُلٌ صَالِحٌ", "english": "Her father-in-law is a righteous man" }
      ]
    }
  ],
